		"description": "<p>At 20th level, you become an avatar of mercy and forgiveness. You gain the following benefits:</p>\n<p><em><strong>Eyes of Mercy.</strong></em> Your @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.my42mip0qc35rcp2]{Lay on Hands} feature can now be used at a range of 30 feet as long as you can see the recipient. In addition, you can spend a minute studying a creature and learn the worst thing that has ever been done to it, and what, if anything, could help it move on.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Voice of Redemption.</em> </strong>You can cast @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-spells.Item.hnvt4tnuww6o4vvi]{Calm Emotions} at will without seen components and without expending spell slots.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Hands of Compassion.</strong></em> Any time you touch a creature, it is subjected to a @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-spells.Item.sgiwn0n20mnf1ddx]{Lesser Restoration} effect. You cannot suppress this effect, but it does work on you. At the start of your turn it automatically affects any creature grappling or grappled by you. Otherwise, to use it in combat requires a bonus action.</p>",
